SECRET SAFETY RULES
Before any commit, run:

git status --short
git diff --cached --name-only
git diff --cached --check

Scan staged content with conservative patterns:

git diff --cached | grep -Ei \
  'api[_-]?key|secret|token|password|passwd|private[_-]?key|BEGIN .*PRIVATE KEY|CF_API|CLOUDFLARE|DATABASE_URL|REDIS_URL|JWT|SESSION_SECRET|WEBHOOK_SECRET' \
  || true

If suspicious content appears:
- stop
- explain in Thai
- unstage the file
- propose .env.example placeholders only

SAFE GIT WORKFLOW
Use this pattern:

cd ~/zeaz-platform
git pull --ff-only

# inspect
git status --short
git diff --stat

# stage only safe files
git add <safe-files>

# verify staged files
git diff --cached --name-only
git diff --cached --check

# run validation
python3 scripts/validate-yaml.py
make yaml-validate
make workflow-validate
git diff --check

# commit
git commit -m "Short English commit message"

# push only after validations pass
git push origin main

If git pull --ff-only fails due to local unstaged changes:
- do not force.
- inspect status.
- either commit safe changes first or stash only safe working changes.
- never stash secrets blindly unless user explicitly accepts.

DANGEROUS COMMAND POLICY
Do not run or suggest these without explicit confirmation and backup plan:
- rm -rf on broad paths
- git reset --hard
- git clean -fdx
- terraform apply
- terraform destroy
- cloudflare token delete/rotate
- bulk DNS mutation
- deleting tunnels
- overwriting .env files
- force push

Cloudflare mutation confirmation phrase should be required:
CONFIRM CLOUDFLARE APPLY

Terraform mutation confirmation phrase should be required:
CONFIRM TERRAFORM APPLY

Git destructive confirmation phrase should be required:
CONFIRM DESTRUCTIVE GIT

YAML VALIDATOR POLICY
Root validator should validate root-owned YAML, but skip imported app-local automation/config directories, including:
- apps/*/.github/**
- apps/*/.copilot/**
- apps/*/.cursor/**
- apps/*/.agents/**
- apps/*/.agent/**
- apps/*/.gemini/**
- apps/*/.claude/**
- apps/*/node_modules/**
- apps/*/.venv/**
- apps/*/venv/**
- apps/*/dist/**
- apps/*/build/**
- apps/*/.next/**
- apps/*/coverage/**
- apps/*/.turbo/**
- apps/*/.cache/**

Rationale:
- imported apps may contain workflows or automation YAML that are not valid for the root platform
- root CI must not break because imported app local automation has custom schema
- app-specific validation can be added later per app

